						               													<description>Theme: In this game you play the role of a farmer who produces wheat, corn, pumpkin or apple and then takes the products to the market to sell. Your goal is to sell your products at the biggest price and earn as much money for your farm, taking care of farm field, weather and law of need and demand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Goal of the game: Goal is to collect as much money as you can.&amp;#10;PLAYER AT THE END OF THE FOURTH ROUND WHO HAS THE MOST MONEY IS THE WINNER.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Mechanics: In the first stage players plant their Products card on the fields. There are seven fields with different values which grant different amount of crops planted on them. When the player in his turn draws a card from the deck card products, he looks it and then put that card on any of the fields. The player can place Products card on an empty field or on a field that already has products on the card itself, taking into account the following order.&amp;#10;Apples can be planted on a corn, corn can be planted over wheat, wheat can be planted over pumpkin and pumpkin can be planted over apples.&amp;#10;Crops get only the player with top card in the field when all Product cards are used.&amp;#10;In second part of the game players take products on market to sell. But must be careful if to many player bring same product price for that product will be very low.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
